00:14:46.410 --> 00:14:50.850
So what is the problem? Why do we need to
do this first of all? From my point of view,

00:14:50.850 --> 00:14:55.139
it's from an air pollution and climate point
of view. Two and a half to three million people

00:14:55.139 --> 00:15:00.339
die every year from air pollution, from cardiovascular
disease, respiratory illness, complications

00:15:00.339 --> 00:15:07.429
from asthma, disease, pneumonia, in fact,
about 15 to 20 percent of these are children

00:15:07.429 --> 00:15:15.089
under five years of age in developing countries.
And this number is growing. And global warming

00:15:15.089 --> 00:15:20.839
is a significant problem whether or not you
believe it, it's true. It's happening. The

00:15:20.839 --> 00:15:25.259
temperature changes today are faster. The
rate of change of temperature today is faster

00:15:25.259 --> 00:15:31.259
than any time since the deglaciation from
the last ice age. And this is a significant

00:15:31.259 --> 00:15:36.360
issue because half of global warming is actually
being hidden or masked by what are called

00:15:36.360 --> 00:15:41.929
cooling pollutant aerosol particles. The particles
that you actually see in the air from pollution

00:15:41.929 --> 00:15:46.170
are hiding half of global warming. So if we
actually clean up all of the air pollution

00:15:46.170 --> 00:15:49.839
particles in the world which we want to do
because these are the ones that cause the

00:15:49.839 --> 00:15:53.709
two and a half to three million deaths, most
of them, then we would actually double global

00:15:53.709 --> 00:15:58.199
warming instantaneously. That's a scary problem.

00:15:58.199 --> 00:16:04.269
The Arctic sea ice is disappearing rapidly
as I'll show you. And this is also scary because

00:16:04.269 --> 00:16:10.079
within 20 years, if it disappears, then there
will be possibly a rapid tipping point where

00:16:10.079 --> 00:16:15.610
there'll be more rapid acceleration of warming.
And populations are increasingly quickly and

00:16:15.610 --> 00:16:20.550
as a result, and there's rising energy demand.
And our current fossil fuel infrastructure,

00:16:20.550 --> 00:16:25.989
the fuels themselves are short-lived. They're
not gonna be here even if we used them all

00:16:25.989 --> 00:16:31.519
for the next 100, 150 years, they're eventually
gonna disappear. We're subject to significant

00:16:31.519 --> 00:16:36.379
price fluctuations. If we go to clean renewable
energy there are no price fluctuations because

00:16:36.379 --> 00:16:37.809
the fuel is free.

