So the solution, we think, is based on scientific
analysis that was done in 2009 before the

00:19:47.789 --> 00:19:54.419
Scientific American article, was what we call
"wind, water, and sun." So what was recommended,

00:19:54.419 --> 00:19:59.429
based on just ignoring the costs at first,
we looked at a bunch of different technologies

00:19:59.429 --> 00:20:03.720
and found that the best ones in terms of their
environmental benefits, in terms of health

00:20:03.720 --> 00:20:12.860
and climate. In terms of catastrophic risk.
